@page "/skills"

<Client.Components.Public.Shared.Navbar />

<main class="container min-vh-90 py-5">
    <div class="row">
        <div class="col">
            <h1 class="mt-3">Skills</h1>

            <p>I have highlighted my key technical skills that I bring to software development.</p>

            <div class="row mt-4">

                <div class="col-md-4 my-2">
                    <div class="card shadow-no-hover">
                        <img src="assets/img/skillsicons/CSharp.png" class="card-img-top" alt="Skill card thumbnail image" />

                        <div class="card-body">
                            <h3 class="card-title fw-bold">C# Programming</h3>

                            <p class="card-text">
                                I use the programming language C# to build websites and web apps.
                                C# enables me to write fast, clean and maintainable code.
                                I'm also well versed in .NET, the ecosystem that C# runs on.
                            </p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="col-md-4 my-2">
                    <div class="card shadow-no-hover">
                        <img src="assets/img/skillsicons/SQLDatabase.png" class="card-img-top" alt="Skill card thumbnail image" />

                        <div class="card-body">
                            <h3 class="card-title fw-bold">Database Development</h3>

                            <p class="card-text">
                                Database development is critical to most projects.
                                I am well versed in SQL development, from queries to design.
                                I can also do code-first databases with Entity Framework.
                            </p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="col-md-4 my-2">
                    <div class="card shadow-no-hover">
                        <img src="assets/img/skillsicons/AspNetBlazor.png" class="card-img-top" alt="Skill card thumbnail image" />

                        <div class="card-body">
                            <h3 class="card-title fw-bold">ASP.NET Core + Blazor</h3>
                            <p class="card-text">
                                I use proven design patterns and frameworks to build websites. 
                                The mature framework ASP.NET with its new addition Blazor fits the bill for most projects.
                                Visit my portfolio to see examples.
                            </p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>

            </div>

            <div class="row my-3">

                <div class="col-md-4 my-2">
                    <div class="card shadow-no-hover">
                        <img src="assets/img/skillsicons/entity-framework-core.png" class="card-img-top" alt="Skill card thumbnail image" />
                        <div class="card-body">
                            <h3 class="card-title fw-bold">Entity Framework Core</h3>
                            <p class="card-text">
                                Entity Framework Core is a lightweight, extensible, and open source version
                                of the popular Entity Framework data access technology. It is an object-relational
                                mapper which enables .NET developers to work with a database using .NET objects.
                            </p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="col-md-4 my-2">
                    <div class="card shadow-no-hover">
                        <img src="assets/img/skillsicons/Azure-AWS.png" class="card-img-top" alt="Skill card thumbnail image" />
                        <div class="card-body">
                            <h3 class="card-title fw-bold">Azure DevOps + AWS EC2</h3>
                            <p class="card-text">
                                I use Azure and AWS to host my applications securely in the cloud.
                                The Azure cloud platform is designed to help developers create new solutions. 
                                Amazon EC2 offers choice of storage, and operating system to help
                                you best match the needs of your workload.
                            </p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="col-md-4 my-2">
                    <div class="card shadow-no-hover">
                        <img src="assets/img/skillsicons/github&bitbucket.png" class="card-img-top" alt="Skill card thumbnail image" />
                        <div class="card-body">
                            <h3 class="card-title fw-bold">Bitbucket + Github</h3>
                            <p class="card-text">
                                Both Bitbucket and Github are Git repository hosting service. They are a collaboration tool built for teams.
                                I have been using both of them on my projects. GitHub revolves around public code while Bitbucket is designed
                                mainly for private projects.
                            </p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="col-md-4 my-2">
                    <div class="card shadow-no-hover">
                        <img src="assets/img/skillsicons/git.png" class="card-img-top" alt="Skill card thumbnail image" />
                        <div class="card-body">
                            <h3 class="card-title fw-bold">Git version control</h3>
                            <p class="card-text">
                                Git is a free and open source distributed version control system designed to handle everything from 
                                small to very large projects with speed and efficiency. It is easy to learn and has a tiny footprint
                                with lightning fast performance.
                            </p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="col-md-4 my-2">
                    <div class="card shadow-no-hover">
                        <img src="assets/img/skillsicons/Bootstrap.png" class="card-img-top" alt="Skill card thumbnail image" />
                        <div class="card-body">
                            <h3 class="card-title fw-bold">Bootstrap Front End Design</h3>
                            <p class="card-text">
                                The look and feel are very important elements to any project. 
                                These days, anything you can view on the web should look good on screens of all sizes.
                                I utilize the Bootstrap framework to bring an attractive and responsive design to web apps.
                            </p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="col-md-4 my-2">
                    <div class="card shadow-no-hover">
                        <img src="assets/img/skillsicons/HTML5CSS3JS.png" class="card-img-top" alt="Skill card thumbnail image" />
                        <div class="card-body">
                            <h3 class="card-title fw-bold">Front End Core Languages</h3>
                            <p class="card-text">
                                I use HTML, CSS and JavaScript to build responsive front ends for websites.
                                This dynamic trio lies at the heart of most web applications you'll find on the web today.
                                Check out my front end work in the portfolio area.
                            </p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>

            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</main>

<Client.Components.Public.Shared.Footer />